Hi everyone! üëã

My name is Amber Wardle, I‚Äôm 19 years old and based in Nottinghamshire, East Midlands.

I‚Äôve always had a real passion for acting and I‚Äôm now at the stage where I‚Äôm starting to explore ways to get my foot in the door of the industry. I joined this group for some inspiration, guidance, and advice from others who are already involved in acting or know the best ways to get started.

From my own judgment, I‚Äôd say my playing age is around 16‚Äì24, though that‚Äôs something I‚Äôm still figuring out and would love some feedback on!

I‚Äôd really appreciate any tips, resources, or recommendations for UK-based acting agents who work with newcomers or people just starting out. I‚Äôm eager to learn, grow, and make the most of any opportunities that come my way.

Thank you so much ‚Äî I‚Äôm looking forward to connecting with everyone and learning from your experiences! üé¨‚ú®

‚Äî Amber Wardle, 19 ü§ç

topComments.text: Register for the open auditions with Nottingham Shakespeare Company. Friendly, open to all, welcoming to everyone with their own unique type of weird (although you don't have to be strange if you don't want to be) üôÇ

Definitely recommend joining either The television workshop or The Actors workshop for training. The TV workshop only goes up to 21 years though. So you‚Äôd only have 1 year with them. 
If you need professional Headshots feel free to drop me a message on Beau-Louise Photography for my Headshot packages. Good luck with your acting journey. X

Hej alle sammen!

Jeg kommer fra Danmark Radio, hvor vi her i Fakta- og Livsstilsafdelingen sidder og caster til et nyt TV-format. Vi leder efter par, som er i tvivl om, hvorvidt de skal have b√∏rn. 

I en verden med et stigende tempo, t√•rnh√∏je f√∏devarepriser, krig i Europa og klimaangst f√•r vi - som vi er blevet tudet √∏rerne fulde af - f√¶rre b√∏rn end nogensinde. Mere pr√¶cist 1,5 barn i stedet for 2,01 barn pr. Kvinde. For at nuancere problematikken har vi brug for nogle modige medvirkende, som t√∏r lukke os ind i deres tvivl. Er det jer?

I kan h√∏re mange flere detaljer om formatet, hvis I skriver til mig p√• tlf. 50906007 eller nedenfor i kommentarsporet. Jeg vil gl√¶de mig til at tale med jer allesammen :) 

De bedste hilsner

Clara Bruun, journalist, DR Aarhus

I kan h√∏re mange flere detaljer om formatet, hvis I skriver til mig p√• tlf. 50906007 eller nedenfor i kommentarsporet. Jeg vil gl√¶de mig til at tale med jer allesammen :) 

De bedste hilsner

Clara Bruun, journalist, DR Aarhus

items.text:
We are casting for an updated tour of the children‚Äôs theatre show, ‚ÄúThe Dinosaur That Pooped a Rock Show‚Äù, based on the popular books by McFly‚Äôs Tom Fletcher and Dougie Poynter. 

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Tom Fletcher & Dougie Poynter and Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions. 

**Production dates:**

Auditions will take place on 24th November 2025

Rehearsals begin on 12th January ‚Äì 22nd January 2026 in London
Tour dates Jan ‚Äì Nov 2026.
We are currently have 91 dates and counting. 

**Production location: **Greater London

**Role: **We are looking for a costume character/ skin artist to play the role of Dino. The artist will need to operate Dino‚Äôs mouth, hands and head, bringing the character to life. They will also be required to join in dance moves and routines whilst inside the costume. We are looking for someone between 5‚Äô6‚Äù and 5‚Äô10‚Äù tall. Previous skin/ costume character experience is essential.

The successful applicant will need to have a full UK drivers licence and will be comfortable driving the touring van on a shared basis with the rest of the company.

Please send CV's & headshots to: casting.mtproductions@gmail.com

**Fees:**

Rehearsal fee: ¬£550pw

Show day fee: ¬£150

Travel day fee: ¬£50

Subsistence: ¬£20

CASTING CALL: Russian speaking actors
ISO Russian speaking male, 30s, in the role of SOLDIER 1 in the short film During Winter, I Thought of My Father by Daniil Vasilyev. 
Breakdown: 

Soldier 1 (30s): An imperial Russian soldier, loyal to his country at any cost, even if it means hunting and killing one of his fellow countrymen. He struggles with the moral challenges presented before him, yet he chooses to close off his heart and simply follow orders. 

Compensation: food and travel provided, IMDB credit and end screen credits. 

Submit by November 21st, 2025 to duringwinter26@gmail.com. Auditions are to be submitted by November 23rd, 2025.

CASTING CALL: Russian speaking actors
ISO Russian speaking male, 30s, in the role of SOLDIER 1 in the short film During Winter, I Thought of My Father by Daniil Vasilyev. 
Breakdown: 

Soldier 1 (30s): An imperial Russian soldier, loyal to his country at any cost, even if it means hunting and killing one of his fellow countrymen. He struggles with the moral challenges presented before him, yet he chooses to close off his heart and simply follow orders. 

Compensation: food and travel provided, IMDB credit and end screen credits. 

Submit by November 21st, 2025 to duringwinter26@gmail.com. Auditions are to be submitted by November 23rd, 2025.

I am a 2nd year film production student at UCA in Farnham, Surrey.

We are currently in the process of trying to find extras for our film that we are shooting in sugar shack (the old pop world) in Portsmouth. Due to the brief we can only have people who are 18+ the dates we will be needing you are the 17th and 19th of November 9am-5pm, dress code will be club attire. As we are only students and have a very limited budget we won‚Äôt be able to pay you for this role but we will provide catering, as well as this you will be mentioned in the credits of the film and this will be submitted to film festivals. If you have any questions or are interested please email me via - maddiewest2006@icloud.com or private message me alternatively you can find me on instagram filmsbymads06.

Thank you.

En mand og en kvinde er de eneste to i publikum til singer/songwriter-koncert. Kvinden sidder, og ser lidt distanceret ud. Trist, nedtrykt. Manden l√¶gger m√¶rke til det, og ville √∏nske, han kunne g√∏re noget ved det. 

Til sidst rejser han sig, og danser (grimt). Viser s√•rbarhed for m√•ske at kunne distrahere kvinden.

Hun rejser sig op, og de danser sammen.

Der er ingen replikker, men det er en fordel, hvis man kan udtrykke sig via mimik.

One More F Christmas is a dark comedy short film about a dysfunctional family gathering that spirals out of control when old resentments, bad cooking, and too much wine collide. What starts as a cheerful Christmas dinner quickly turns into pure chaos

The brutally honest grandma who never filters her thoughts. Equal parts loving and impossible. Thinks she‚Äôs helping, but somehow always makes things worse. A sharp comedic role that blends warmth, wit, and a bit of chaos

‚ú®** CASTING CALL (Denver, CO) **‚ú®
Hey everyone! I‚Äôm casting for my first web series, **A Fish Outta Water**, shooting in Denver in late January 2026. I‚Äôm looking for **three Black women (18‚Äì24)** for the lead and supporting roles.

**Characters:**

Riley - Black woman - She is a quiet girl, the type to blend right into the wall. Riley has a hard time understanding math (who doesn‚Äôt?) and finds it difficult to make friends at school. Her best friend and confidant is her pet goldfish, Shanice.

Shanice - Black woman - A former goldfish and current ghost-girl. Shanice spent her goldfish life as Riley‚Äôs only friend; she knows everything about her. More importantly, she knows how to help her in her new ghost-girl form.

Issa - Black woman - Riley‚Äôs classmate. Issa is strong-willed and hopes others notice this within her. Deep down, she longs to connect with her peers, just like Riley.

If you‚Äôre interested, please submit through the form below ‚Äî it only takes a minute:
üîó https://forms.gle/QVpJUmzZjAjQE5W18

Feel free to share this with friends who act! Let‚Äôs make something dope together üíôüé¨

sharedPost.text:
Atomic Theatre Wheat Ridge CO, presents:

Reading With The Rabbits a two-part youth theatre program designed to nurture young performers and inspire a love of literacy in the community.

Part One: Tween & Teen Performers
We provide tween and teen actors with a platform to showcase their character work, voice acting, and stage presence in front of a live audience. Using picture books as the medium, performers present their own directorial vision of a story of their choosing. Each show features 4‚Äì5 different stories, ensemble songs, and theatre games.

In a world where teen actors are often limited by age, gender, physical type, or busy school and sports schedules, Reading with the Rabbits offers a flexible, creative space to experiment and play.

Upcoming Auditions

Date: December 10

Time: 6-8PM

Location: Wheat Ridge Grange 

Performances: Saturday December13 at 1:30 and 3:30 

Theme: Winter 
J√≥lab√≥kafl√≥√∞i√∞ (book flood)

Actors will be given a stipend for their time. 

Audition Prep: reserve an audition time slot by emailing atomictheatreinc@gmail.com 

Actors are expected  to come with a performance ready picture  book to entertain young children and their families. Be perpared to show the book during  your staged reading.  You are the director/ actor and MC. Show off your different characters, find games within the pages, incorporate music or movement, break the fourth wall and invite the audience into your imagination. 

We appreciate your creativity and attention to detail, and can‚Äôt wait to experience your theatrical offering.

Be prepared to learn a sing-along song, minor choreography, and an improv game that will be played with the ensemble during the performances

Part Two: Community Story Hours
These donation-based performances are free and open to the public. Each event features:

Storytime performances where new readers watch older kids bring books to life.

Photo opportunities

Themed crafts to make the experience extra engaging for families.

* Usually bunnies who demonstrate how to be good audience members with their listening ears.  Our December showcase will be around a bonfire at a local urban farm weather permitting. The goats and chickens will be standing in for the rabbits.

items.text:
Hello everyone,

My name is Kayuran Moodley, and I am the founder of KM PICTURES, a newly established mobile film production based in Chatsworth, Durban. I‚Äôm currently in the process of expanding my team and looking for dedicated individuals to join me on this creative journey.

At this stage, I am specifically looking for:
üé• Camera Operator ‚Äì someone passionate about cinematography, able to work creatively with mobile or professional cameras, and interested in learning and experimenting with visual storytelling.
‚úÇÔ∏è Video Editor ‚Äì someone skilled in editing, sound design, and color grading, with a good eye for pacing, emotion, and storytelling (experience in horror or suspense genres will be an advantage).

KM PICTURES was started with a simple but powerful goal ‚Äî to create meaningful stories from small beginnings, using whatever tools and talent we have available. I believe in teamwork, creativity, and growth. This is a zero-budget project for now, but it‚Äôs built on passion, vision, and the goal of developing something great together from the ground up.

I‚Äôm currently working on my latest film script, and I want to collaborate with individuals who are serious about learning, growing, and being part of a local production that has the potential to expand into something bigger.

If you‚Äôre a filmmaker, editor, or someone who simply loves the art of storytelling and wants to build a future in film, I would love to connect with you. Let‚Äôs grow this production together and create something unique in the South African film space.

üìç Preferred Location: Chatsworth / Durban (for easier travel and teamwork)
üíº Production: Mobile Film (Independent / Zero Budget)
üìû Contact: 061 046 3076

Let‚Äôs bring creativity to life ‚Äî together.
‚Äî Kayuran Moodley
Founder & Director
KM PICTURES üé•

Do you ever feel resistant to the business side of acting? You‚Äôre definitely not alone. It‚Äôs the part that I struggle the most with, but like it or not, it‚Äôs part of the journey. And it very often matters more than talent. 

In this video, my friend Jodie Bentley dives into the time-and-creativity struggle ‚Äî that frustrating loop where you want to create but tell yourself there‚Äôs no time, which leads to inaction or perfectionism. She also shares how recognising that ‚Äúno time‚Äù excuse can help break the cycle and bring the joy back into creating.

üé• Watch the video here: [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XzDLqLTATCk](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XzDLqLTATCk)

## üé© Casting Call

**Event Theme:** Cultural Exchange Private Event
**Date:** Tuesday, 18 November 2025 (morning)
**Location:** Private Members Club, Central London
**Payment:** Paid + A dinner in the private club

üìú Role Description

We are recruiting **3 performers** to take part in an exclusive cultural event in Central London, portraying distinguished **business guests** attending a formal reception.

**Total Roles:**
* üë©‚Äçüíº Two female participants (elegant, poised, well-presented)
* üë®‚Äçüíº One male participant (gentlemanly, confident, well-spoken)

**Requirements:**
* Age: 25‚Äì45
* Dress Code: Business formal 
* Appearance: Professional, confident, naturally engaging
* No dialogue required ‚Äî participants will engage in natural conversation 

üì∏ How to Apply

Please submit the following information:
1. **One recent formal photo** (full or half body)
2. **A short self-introduction video (30‚Äì60 seconds)** including:
   * Name and profession
   * English proficiency or performance experience (if any)
   * A brief personal introduction

Videos can be recorded on a phone ‚Äî simple background and good lighting are sufficient. Please send them to staff.isunshine@gmail.com

items.text:
Hi my names Lucas, im 19 and based in Leeds I am wanting to succeed as an actor but i am finding it hard looking for work to help me get noticed by agencies and things like that. I have done some practice with voice over lessons and learned about self tapes and getting help from industry pros. I know its a pretty difficult industry however i am set on achieving it. If any student films or minor projects needing actors want to connect i am ok with it in exchange for footage. University or college information is required for safety purposes. I am willing to go further than just Leeds to help me grow my profile and i am looking for collaborations both paid and unpaid (please nothing rude or unsolicited). Also i like to do music and write lyrics so if there are any music students or collaborators interested in writing music too then get in touch! I do have support, so will run it by them but please do reach out if you think we could work together.

topComments.text: I know you want to get into acting straight away. But you can go about it by becoming an SA. Sign up to a tv and casting agency in your area. Many SA's have had lines, walk on's, get noticed by casting directors. They keep a note of you and will book you again if they like your work. SA's can get many opportunities to feature if they are picked. So try getting in that way. Once you build up a profile, get experience, get to know people. The roles will follow.
It‚Äôll be great to work with you. I‚Äôm a filmmaker based in Huddersfield and often film in Leeds

I am a 2nd year film production student at UCA in Farnham, Surrey.

We are currently in the process of trying to find extras for our film that we are shooting in sugar shack (the old pop world) in Portsmouth. Due to the brief we can only have people who are 18+ the dates we will be needing you are the 17th and 19th of November 9am-5pm, dress code will be club attire. As we are only students and have a very limited budget we won‚Äôt be able to pay you for this role but we will provide catering, as well as this you will be mentioned in the credits of the film and this will be submitted to film festivals. If you have any questions or are interested please email me via - maddiewest2006@icloud.com or private message me alternatively you can find me on instagram filmsbymads06.

Thank you.

üé• Szukasz podno≈õnika lub d≈∫wigu na plan filmowy?

Z nami zrobisz ujƒôcia z wysoko≈õci, zamontujesz o≈õwietlenie lub przestawisz scenografiƒô bez stresu i op√≥≈∫nie≈Ñ! Dzia≈Çamy lokalnie ‚Äì Krak√≥w i okolice, ale dojedziemy te≈º na inne plany.

‚û°Ô∏è Podno≈õniki koszowe do 70 m ‚Äì dla kamer, operator√≥w, o≈õwietleniowc√≥w.

My name is Marcello Balena, and I'm an Italian saxophonist, composer, and arranger.

My musical experience, both live and in the studio, ranges from jazz/fusion and rock to house music, smooth jazz, and chill out.

I'm available should there be an opportunity to work with your company.

Below is some information.

I am a 2nd year film production student at UCA in Farnham, Surrey.

We are currently in the process of trying to find extras for our film that we are shooting in sugar shack (the old pop world) in Portsmouth. Due to the brief we can only have people who are 18+ the dates we will be needing you are the 17th and 19th of November 9am-5pm, dress code will be club attire. As we are only students and have a very limited budget we won‚Äôt be able to pay you for this role but we will provide catering, as well as this you will be mentioned in the credits of the film and this will be submitted to film festivals. If you have any questions or are interested please email me via - maddiewest2006@icloud.com or private message me alternatively you can find me on instagram filmsbymads06.

Thank you.

EMERGENCY CAST CALL! VOLUNTEER ONLY

Hello everyone, my name is Cian and I am a level 6 film student at the University of Staffordshire, putting together my final year project, Metalhead.

Until recently, I had an actor attached to play the role of a doctor in my film. That actor cannot find the time for my shoot dates any longer, so i put the question to you.

Can you fill the role of a doctor for my project? Can you play an overworked, stern authority figure who can give the protagonist bad news?

My shoot date is Monday 10th November, filming in Stoke-on-Trent from 11am-5pm. Please let me know if this works for you!

If you think you can do this, please get in touch at:

Cian4472@hotmail.co.uk 

Or 

07722 490116 

Happy to provide anyone with more project details.

Bereits hierbei sehen wir es als √§u√üerst fraglich  an, dass bei einer deutschen Kinoproduktion alle Filmschaffende also auch die Schauspieler und das gesamte Team nach den in Spanien √ºblichen Tarifen und K√ºnstlergagen abgerechnet wird.
Zumal sich die Anfrage insgesamt auf eher Deutsche Touristen bezieht.

Im in Deutschland geschalteten Gesuch ist m√∂glicherweise auch daher keinerlei Angabe zur Gage zu finden. So m√ºssen m√∂gliche Bewerber  erstmal von keinerlei Gage und damit auch nicht von der in Spanien √ºblichen Gage ausgehen.

Dazu dann noch die unglaublich klingende Info im Gesuch ab Donnerstag 06.11.25
"Keine √úbernahme der Reisekosten."  und sich bereits Montag bis Donnerstag 10.11 -14.11.25  auch Nachts zu Verf√ºgung zustellen. 

Wobei die Nachtdrehs im Gesuch erstmal verschwiegen wurden ebenso, wie zumindest der ungef√§hre Drehort einer sehr gro√üen Insel, bei eben  keiner Erstattung der Reisekosten.

Bereits in den ersten Stunden sorgte die Suchanzeige f√ºr gro√üe Emp√∂rung in den verschiedensten Gruppierungen Filmschaffender. Auch und ganz besonders auf der hauseigenen Facebookseite von CONSTANTIN FILM √§u√üerten zahlreiche Filmfans ihre Best√ºrzung √ºber  das respektlose Vorgehen der Verantwortlichen.
Gleichzeitig verfassten und sendeten wir den nun folgenden Offenen Brief direkt  an  die Hauptverantwortlichen von CONSTANTIN FILM.

 Kurze Zeit sp√§ter wurde die Suchanzeige samt aller √ºberwiegend ver√§rgerter Kommentare komplett gel√∂scht.
(Beitrag und Auswahl einiger Kommentare wurden jedoch vorher von Faire Gagen gesichert)

Auch mit dieser kommentarlosen L√∂schung, der sicherlich verst√§ndlichen Kritik sehr vieler Fimschaffender best√§tigt sich leider ein zunehmend abgek√ºhlter Kurs mit fehlender Augenh√∂he zu Ihren Komparsen seitens CONSTANTIN FILM.

Scheinbar versucht man jegliche Kritik der Filmschaffenden  m√∂glichst zu ignorieren und auszul√∂schen, statt sich dieser Kritik - auch  aus dem eigenen Lager - zu stellen. 

Kern unserer Kritik ist also der insgesamt zunehmend respektlose Umgang seitens CONSTANTIN FILM  in einem  dazugeh√∂renden Gewerk einer jeden Produktion. Der Komparserie.

Daher auch nun erstmals ein "Offener Brief" an die Verantwortlichen von CONSTANTIN FILM, der fairerweise bereits seit Freitag d. 07. November dort vorliegt und auf  ein Statement wartet.

Offener Brief der Filmschaffenden
Initiative "Faire Gagen"

Liebe Frau Kindermann,
Lieber Herr Berben,

Erst k√ºrzlich hatten wir Sie √ºber die Ver√§rgerung tausender Filmschaffender im Fall "EBERHOFFER-Krimi" (Kinofilmproduktion) unterrichtet.
 
150 Kompars*innen sollten keine Gage f√ºr ihre Arbeit am Set bekommen obwohl hier neben, der einfach √ºblichen Gage auch der gesetzliche Mindestlohn greift.

Die meist unwissenden Menschen wurden daraufhin doch noch fair und damit gesetzeskonform von Constantin Film bezahlt.
 
Nun berichten uns schon wieder ganz aktuell viele Filmschaffende √ºber ihren und damit auch unseren erneuten Unmut.

Diesmal handelt es sich um die Constantin Film Produktion "DER PERFEKTE URLAUB" der z.Z. auf Mallorca gedreht wird.

Das Gesuch wurde vor nicht mal 24 Stunden von Constantin Film in den sozialen Netzwerken geschaltet.
Im Gesuch werden jedoch bereits f√ºr die kommende Woche ab Montag (10.11.25 bis 14.11.25) Kompars*innen auf Mallorca gesucht.

+++ Constantin Film √ºbernimmt dabei keinerlei Reisekosten. Auch eine Gage ist ganz offensichtlich nicht vorgesehen. Lediglich die √úbernachtung und eine eh √ºbliche Verpflegung wird √ºbernommen +++

Zus√§tzlich soll es sich nach unseren Informationen, auch noch um erfahrungsgem√§√ü sehr anstrengende Nachtdrehszeiten handeln.

Auch, dass die gebuchten Filmschaffenden sich bereits Montag, irgendwo auf Mallorca (keinerlei Angaben zum Drehort im Gesuch) befinden sollen sieht unsere Anh√§gerschaft und hiermit auch wir - die Initiative Faire Gagen - als hochgradig respektlos an.

Warum werden diese Menschen nicht wie bei anderen, sogar wesentlich weniger Budget-starken Produktionen fair bezahlt und bereits im Gesuch wie sonst √ºblich umfassend informiert und  allein damit schon mal wesentlich respektvoller behandelt.

Augenscheinlich entsteht hier der
 Eindruck, dass Constantin Film die gebuchten Menschen eher als Ware ansieht, eine Ware, die man √§hnlich wie Requisiten m√∂glichst schnell via Express Lieferung, (aber zudem auch noch weitestgehend kostenlos) ordert um eine Millionenschwere Filmproduktion noch irgendwie und irgendwo, kurzfristig und billig zu retten.

Auch bei der gerade im Kino laufenden Produktion "PUMUCKL" mussten
wiederum dank unserer Initiative ca 200 Filmschaffende erst nachtr√§glich, gesetzeskonform bezahlt werden. 
Dazu ist der bereits oben  genannte EDERHOFFER Kinofilm-Skandal unserer Anh√§ngerschaft noch in den K√∂pfen.

Der nun neue, dritte Fall zeigt leider eindrucksvoll auf, dass  Constantin Film offensichtlich diese exorbitanten Verstimmungen (auch Ihrer vielen, eigenen Kompars*innen) nicht sonderlich ernst nimmt,  ja, dass man dies sogar mit einplant und dann (notfalls sp√§ter) doch noch ggfs. fair bezahlt, falls der eigene  Sparplan wieder eher nach hinten losgehen sollte.

Ansonsten k√∂nnen wir uns diesen erneuten v√∂llig unn√∂tigen Eklat nur noch damit erkl√§ren dass es wom√∂glich mit der Kommunikation im eigenen Hause zumindest, was einen respektvollen Umgang mit uns Filmschaffenden betrifft, leider nicht zum Besten steht.

Jedenfalls werden wir durch die H√§ufung der genannten Unmutsf√§lle  den Eindruck nicht los, dass sich Ihre Einsparversuche insbesondere auf das vermeintlich schw√§chste Glied der Filmproduktionsgewerke konzentrieren soll.

Frei nach dem Motto:

"Die Deppen machen das auch umsonst"

Ein wirklich sehr trauriger Eindruck der hier gerade unter vielen Filmschaffenden zunehmend Nahrung findet und der auch in Ihrem eigenen Interesse umgehend entkr√§ftet werden sollte.

Initiative, Faire Gagen
(mehr als 2900 Filmschaffende und viele weitere uns angeschlossene und folgende Communities und Facebook -Gruppen)

Ansprechpartner: Klaus Stutzer 
"Faire Gagen" Redaktion
Claudia Raquet und Klaus Stutzer

https://www.facebook.com/share/17WttEsKan/

 ***

"Offener Brief" Ende

Liebe Filmschaffende, es geht hier nicht nur um CONSTANTIN FILM sondern um unsere Arbeit ganz allgemein und sicherlich nicht nur um die Komparserie, sondern eben auch ganz allgemein um eine respektvolle Entlohnung f√ºr den ganzen Filmsektor. 
Hierf√ºr ist unserer wichtigste Eigenschaft eine m√∂glichst uneingeschr√§nkte Solidarit√§t im kompletten Filmsektor und dies nicht nur in Deutschland, wie uns hier auch die √ºblichen Gagen in anderen L√§ndern leider beweisen.

+++ Eigentlich sollte es doch keinerlei Rolle spielen, welchen Job wir alle f√ºr unsere  Filme bew√§ltigen. Ob Produktionsleitung, Regie, Haupdarsteller, Beleuchter oder Casting Agenturen, ob Caterer Setrunner, Stra√üenblocker, Fahrer oder Komparsen und all die anderen beteiligten und sehr wichtigen Menschen einer Filmproduktion. Und nicht zuletzt auch die Filmf√∂rderung, die uns mit √ºpigen Geldern, guten  Gewissens bez√ºglich Nachghaltigkeit, aber auch Fairnesses die Produktionen unterst√ºtzt.

Alle erledigen ihren  Job f√ºr unsere oft so guten Film-Produktionen und alle wollen f√ºr ihre  Arbeit zumindest respektiert werden.

Mindestens genauso wichtig sind unsere Konsumenten also unsere Zuschauer im Kino und zu Hause. Besonders sie  sind ungeheuer wichtig und daher auch gefragt, wenn  sie von fehlender Fairness und Respektlosigkeit im Arbeitsleben erfahren. Auch daher unsere Entscheidung  zu einem "Offenen Brief"

+++ Vielen Dank f√ºr Eure Solidarit√§t  und vielen Dank f√ºrs Teilen, Liken,  Kommentieren und sonst irgendwie verbreiten +++

AUDITION CALL ‚Äî DIRT‚Äôs ‚ÄúMIDNIGHT‚ÄôS DREAM: UNE SOIR√âE ENCHANT√âE‚Äù

Paid, 3-month Contract | Circus ‚Ä¢ Variety ‚Ä¢ Cabaret

Denver Immersive Repertory Theater (DIRT) is casting non-Union talent for MIDNIGHT‚ÄôS DREAM: UNE SOIR√âE ENCHANT√âE √Ä LA JOLIE MAISON, an intimate circus cabaret that exists as a show-within-a-show in the world of MIDNIGHT‚ÄôS DREAM, a 10,000 square foot, open-box immersive theater piece. We are filling 4 featured roles for our circus cabaret ensemble:

1 Emcee - vocalist, ideally with a circus or variety act
2 Solo Ground Specialty Acts - circus, variety, or vocal performance
1 Solo Aerial Act - performers with multiple skills on the ground and in the air preferred

‚∏ª

Who We‚Äôre Looking For

Solo acts in any circus or variety discipline: aerial, juggling, contortion, handbalance, clown, acrobatics, etc ‚Äî plus singers with strong stage presence.

An Emcee who can deliver scripted and sung lines with charisma, connect with the audience, and perform a circus or variety act.
Acts must be adaptable to music selected by the production team.

‚∏ª

The Show

An intimate cabaret experience for approximately 50 audience members per performance.

Stage size: 14 x 12 ft

Aerial point - low height, approximately 12ft

No fire or animals permitted.

‚∏ª

What You‚Äôll Bring

1‚Äì3 solo acts (5‚Äì7 minutes each) adaptable to our chosen music.

A performance style that can range from family-friendly to burlesque-adjacent, as long as it is polished and engaging.

Strong stage presence, timing, and audience connection.

‚∏ª
The Gig

Must have access to Denver local housing

Contract: 3-month independent contractor agreement with option to extend.

Performance Pay: $200 per performance - 2 acts per show + additional staging/choreography - 2 shows per night. 6 performances per week (W-F evenings, Sat matinee, Sat-Sunday evenings)

Rehearsal rate: $25 per hour

Rehearsal Dates (including tech/dress): March 23-April 9, 2026

Performance Dates: April 10-July 12, 2026

Rehearsal and Performance Location: DIRT - 1431 15th St, Denver
‚∏ª
How to Audition

Please submit to the Google Form (it will include):

1. Video(s) of the exact act(s) you would perform (or a showreel if not available).
YouTube/Vimeo links preferred

2. Headshot

3. Short performer bio (150 words max)

4. List of circus/variety/vocal skills

5. Technical/rigging requirements

Apply via our Google Form:
https://docs.google.com/.../1FAIpQLScXXQlG4iM.../viewform...

Submission Deadline: 11/21/25 / Ongoing
First round of casting decided by: December 10, 2025
Conceived and Written by Steve Wargo
Directed by Amber Blais

items.text:
Hi friends! I have a question for the group (especially for agents and casting, but also anyone)! I started acting seriously 20 years ago, when I was a kid. I started in theatre, have impressive training/education, pivoted to film 10 years ago, then took an extensive break. Last year I recommitted and spent a fair amount of time reacquainting myself with the industry and where it is. Updated headshots, portfolio shots, resume, self tape equipment, renewed memberships to the three main casting resources, etc. This year I booked a couple of live performances and a whole bunch of commercial work, several featured background, a costar, a short film lead, a short film supporting, and im about to film my first vertical as a supporting role. Here‚Äôs my issue/question:

I know we are heading into a slow season and I wanted to use this time to focus on getting representation. BUT I‚Äôve only seen one project. I don‚Äôt have a reel and that‚Äôs kind of important. I have a decent resume, imdb credits, and have made a lot of connections this year. I‚Äôve put a ‚Äúreel‚Äù together of past self tape clips, but I really need some professional footage. I‚Äôm not sure what to do. Is it appropriate to email production for footage? If so, how long after filming should I wait before asking? If not, or if footage isn‚Äôt available yet, what is the most professional thing to do? Specifically focusing on what agents/agencies would prefer. 

Thanks for any help!

Updated headshots, portfolio shots, resume, self tape equipment, renewed memberships to the three main casting resources, etc. This year I booked a couple of live performances and a whole bunch of commercial work, several featured background, a costar, a short film lead, a short film supporting, and im about to film my first vertical as a supporting role. Here‚Äôs my issue/question:

items.text:
Let‚Äôs be real for a moment‚Ä¶ üì∏

Headshots can sometimes feel like an extortionate expense - as a fellow actor, I get it. That‚Äôs why I keep my pricing fair, accessible, and realistic, without ever cutting corners on quality.

I see plenty of novice photographers grab a basic camera & kit lens then start offering ‚Äútoo good to be true‚Äù sessions in these groups for ¬£30‚Äì¬£100 promising they‚Äôll get you seen ‚Ä¶ but here‚Äôs the truth: Headshot photography is a specialist skill. Low end, inexpensive ‚Äúquick fix‚Äù sessions might seem attractive at first but buy cheap, buy twice. 

Invest in a real headshot session with an award-winning photographer who brings experience, artistry, and skill to the table and get it right the first time. I‚Äôm a working actor too so I‚Äôm in your shoes and evolve with the times to provide the most updated, admired form of headshots.

Expect powerful, cinematic portraits that casting directors always notice. Clients regularly tell me their new headshots have led to more auditions, more callbacks and booked work - that‚Äôs exactly what I aim for.

I‚Äôve had my fair share of awkward shoots; rushed sessions with cash grab cameramen who treated me like cattle, just another face passing through‚Ä¶ I started doing this job to change that.
When you book with me, it‚Äôs never rushed. We‚Äôll have a coffee, chat about your goals, play some tunes, and get you relaxed before the camera even comes out. My direction is creative and unorthodox - I‚Äôll get you talking, laughing, and thinking, so we capture real moments that show who YOU are, not just what you look like.

The results speak for themselves - my clients have gone on to appear in major TV shows, films, high-end commercials, and even land roles on the West End. Your headshot is often your first impression - let‚Äôs make sure it‚Äôs unforgettable.

üëâ View my portfolio: https://www.fandmmedia.co.uk/ryan-s-gallery

üëâ Book a showreel scene, cinematic monologue recording, self tape sessions & more: https://www.fandmmedia.co.uk

üé≠ On Spotlight? Enjoy ¬£10 off any package!

Ryan üì∏

F&M Media üèÜ Award-winning headshots that get you seen.

Actors! Tired of hearing ‚Äúthanks for that‚Äù (and nothing else) after auditions? 

Awful right? Humiliating even. 

This is for you.

In our FREE ACTING CLASS you‚Äôll learn how to create UNFORGETTABLE CHARACTERS.

We‚Äôre coaching you on a very simple technique that you can put into your work right away and improve these 3 things:

How to give depth to a character

How to bring the scene alive

How to make castable choices NO ONE else is making

Stella Adler said, ‚ÄúYour talent is in your imagination, not your memory.‚Äù

Actors who train their imagination? They light up the screen.

We‚Äôll show you a simple on-the-spot exercise that flips your scene from flat to electric ‚ö°Ô∏è

 It‚Äôs fun and it‚Äôs FREE. Remember you‚Äôre one audition away from a life-changing role. 

üïß 12:30 PM Pacific (Hollywood time) ‚Äî Live on Zoom

https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88209960827?pwd=5lAKHO7q6BLZzEaCmGaGxORdja9CKq.1

Passcode: ACTING 

 Grab your water, your notebook, and your wildest dream.

üëâ You could keep on getting  ‚Äúgood notes.‚Äù 

Or  üëâ start doing the work that gets good bookings.

 xo KC & Donna-Marie

items.text:
**CALL FOR SOUND & LIGHTING BOARD Operators**

**Production:** *George Orwell‚Äôs 1984*
**Produced by:** PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS
**Location:** Three Stories Theater
937 Liberty Ave, Downtown Pittsburgh
**Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025
**Contact:** playboxpgh@gmail.com

**PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS** is seeking a **Sound Board Operator** and a **Lighting Board Operator** for our upcoming production of *1984* by George Orwell, directed by M.A.C. This is a new concept for this story, completely Americanized through costumes, set design, sound, and overall aesthetic.

Our **full cast and crew of over 30 people** have already been hard at work bringing this show to life over the past few months. We have a complete design and stage management team in place; we are now looking for skilled operators to help us execute this ambitious and timely production during tech week and performances.

**POSITION DETAILS**
**Titles:** Sound Board Operator and Lighting Board Operator
**Compensation Type:** Volunteer / Possible post-show stipend
*(We want to be transparent: this is a volunteer position, but if funds allow, a small stipend may be available after the production.)*

**Dates & Commitment:**
* **Rehearsals (all optional for operators):** Sundays, 6‚Äì9 PM starting August 3, 2025
Trust Arts Education Center ‚Äî 807 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Tech Week:** November 24 ‚Äì December 3, 2025 (dark day on Thanksgiving) ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025 (5 performances total)
Three Stories Theater ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA

We‚Äôre happy to work with your schedule. Please include any known conflicts when reaching out.

**QUALIFICATIONS**
* For Sound: Experience with QLab or a similar playback system
* For Lighting: Familiarity with ETC lighting consoles preferred
* Reliable, communicative, and calm under pressure
* Comfortable collaborating with an awesome stage management and design team! 

**TO APPLY**
Please email **playboxpgh@gmail.com** with:
* Resume (or a brief summary of your relevant experience) **This is super important, since we are using a Pittsburgh Cultural Trust space. They require a review of your resume to let you use the theatre tech equipment.*
* Availability during tech week and performances

If interested, we‚Äôll be in touch right away to discuss next steps.

Thank you!

Marc Palombo
PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS
